{{Wireless embedded system |brand=Ruckus Wireless |model=ZoneFlex 7372 |asin=B00EZWUGOO;US; |manuf_country=China |is_manuf=No |type=access point |fcc_id=S9GZF7372 |fcc_date=11/11/2012 |ic_id=5912A-ZF7372 |pwr_v=12 |pwr_amp=1 |pwr_conn=barrel |pwr_poe=af |cpu1_brand=Atheros |cpu1_model=AR9344;AR9344-BC2A; |fla1=32 MiB |fla1_brand=Spansion |fla1_model=FL256SAIFR0 |ram1=128 MiB |ram1_brand=ESMT |ram1_model=M14D5121632A-2.5B |ram1_num=2 |wi1_chip1_brand=Atheros |wi1_chip1_model=AR9344;AR9344-BC2A; |wi1_802dot11_protocols=bgn |wi1_ant_conn=U.FL,RP-SMA |wi1_txchains=2 |wi1_rxchains=2 |wi1_sstreams=2 |wi2_chip1_brand=Atheros |wi2_chip1_model=AR9582;AR9582-AR1A; |wi2_802dot11_protocols=an |wi2_ant_conn=U.FL,RP-SMA |wi2_txchains=2 |wi2_rxchains=2 |wi2_sstreams=2 |eth_cpu=true |eth_chip2_brand=Atheros |eth_chip2_model=AR8035-A |lan_speed=1G |lan_ports=2 |802dot11_protocols=abgn |default_ip=192.168.0.1 |default_user=super |default_pass=sp-admin |oui=8C:0C:90 |oui_eth=8C:0C:90 }} {{TagLine|ZoneFlex 7372 802.11n Wi-Fi Indoor Access Point}} :[https://www.ruckuswireless.com/products/access-points/zoneflex-indoor/zoneflex-7372-7352 Product page]
*"ST. BERNARD" and the ''Ruckus Wireless'' (barking dog) logo is :silkscreened on the non-SoC side of the board in the FCC photos.
*The device would seem to be using an AR934x SoC (AR9344) and :an additional AR93xx (AR9382/AR9582 or AR9392/AR9592) radio.
1x 10/100/1000 port (PoE), 1x 10/100 port :Default settings are per the FCC label.
Per MAC labels affixed to the FCC EUT (internal and label), the device :is presumed to use (at least) a 8C:0C:90 (''Ruckus Wireless'') OUI.
*[http://www.embeddedworks.net/wlan616c.html ''Ruckus Wireless ZoneFlex 7372'' on '''EmbeddedWorks'''] *[http://rts-bg.com/en/indoor/421-zoneflex-7372-7352.html ''Ruckus Wireless ZoneFlex 7372'' on '''RTS-Computer''']
